Description: Direwolf TNC network interface manager
 dw-iface packages Direwolf and tncattach into a single command that brings
 up a point-to-point IP link over any radio supported by Direwolf's AX.25
 modem (1200 baud AFSK or 2400 baud QPSK).
 .
 A single config file controls the audio device, PTT method, callsign,
 IP address, and CSMA parameters.  'dw-iface up' starts Direwolf, attaches
 tncattach, and configures the network interface.  A systemd unit manages
 the service across reboots.
 .
 Tested with Icom IC-705 and IC-7300 on Ubuntu 24.04.

